						<div class="postbody">Add a read buffer that stuff go directly to the CPU when you read, as when you reset the address, the buffer to read gets filled with I believe the last write to the PPU. See the bottom of the wiki:
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU_registers">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU_registers</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />I'm not sure what the internal buffer is, my guess is the last write, but let somebody else who really knows answer that. And also, keep in mind it's not for the palette range, those are directly read back, no buffer.</div>

