				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It's probably because the PPU can't complete the read within the time that the CPU expects, so it reads to a buffer and then returns that buffer on the next read. On the Apple IIGS, the interface to wave RAM has the same delayed-read behavior.
<br />
<br />Is it documented what mixing reads and writes leaves in the buffer? Or what mixing $0000-$3EFF reads and palette ($3F00-$3FFF) reads leaves? Or what rendering leaves?</div>

